# NOTE 2026-06-24 PM (corrected): the /.netlify/* path prefix is RESERVED by
# Netlify and cannot be the SOURCE of a custom redirect ("path field must not
# start with /.netlify"). The original fallback proxy rules here were INVALID
# and silently dropped at deploy time. All sanatorio functions are now reached
# either via:
#   (a) local function files in el-sanatorio/netlify/functions/* (e.g.
#       sanatorio-availability.mjs) — served at /.netlify/functions/<name>
#       directly without needing a redirect, OR
#   (b) the /api/sanatorio-* aliases above which DO work as proxies.
# So the catch-all /.netlify/* rules are removed. Do not re-add.

